  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CD: &#x201C;Allanando el camino&#x201D;: Women and LGBT people paving a path from justice and memory toward sustai</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Applying UN Resolutions on Gender, Peace and Security, this project capacitates and strengthens the role of women and LGBT people in the most conflict-affected departments, tackling barriers of discrimination and exclusion. A timely intervention, the project supports the transition from justice, memory and collective emotional reparations to catalyse pathways toward sustainable peace and enhance the influence of LGBT people, Afro-Colombian and indigenous women in decision-making, at the territorial and national level, advocating for social change and peace in territorial planning. This 3 pillar approach of social cohesion, development and justice, intervenes at the institutional, community and individual level, bolstering the implementation of the Final Peace Agreement (FPA).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">It is a UNPBF Project which implementation is in charge of three Colombia patners. Proyecto Colombia Diversa is mainly in charge of: Development of virtual depositories of memories about violence and resistance of women and LGBT people. Micro-grants to community-based and faith groups for innovative initiatives of memory reconstruction. Selection and presentation of legal cases and experiences to the SIVJRNR. Strategic litigation before national and international judicial bodies, and before ordinary and transitional justice. Follow-up of legal cases and reports by women and LGBT people in the SIVJRNR.</narrative>
  </description>
